                                                        
•	Networks are categorized based on coverage area

1. Local Area Network (LAN)
•	Uses Ethernet cables or Wi-Fi.
•	Covers a small geographic area (home, office, campus).
•	Example: A small office with 10 computers and printers connected via Ethernet cables.

2. Metropolitan Area Network (MAN)
•	Covers a metropolitan area like a city or town.
•	Example: City cable network.

3. Wide Area Network (WAN)
•	Covers a large geographic area (state, country).
•	Example: The Internet.

4. Wireless Local Area Network (WLAN)
•	Connects devices wirelessly using Wi-Fi technology.
•	Example: A coffee shop with a Wi-Fi network for customers.

5. Personal Area Network (PAN)
•	Connects devices within a few meters.

Examples:
•	Wireless earbuds connected to a smartphone.
•	Laptop connected to a wireless printer.
•	Smartwatch connected to a smartphone.
•	Wireless keyboard connected to a laptop.
